# Quality gates — doc-raiz / BR Validators

> **Non-negotiable:** 0 ESLint errors, 0 ESLint warnings, 100% coverage on `packages/br-validators/src/**`.

## Before every PR or commit with code changes

Run from repo root:

```bash
pnpm lint              # ESLint — must exit 0, --max-warnings 0
pnpm typecheck         # TypeScript — all packages
pnpm test:coverage     # br-validators + CLI — library must be 100%
pnpm build             # all packages compile
```

**Do not merge** if any command fails.

## Lint policy

| Rule | Requirement |
|------|-------------|
| ESLint errors | **0** |
| ESLint warnings | **0** (`--max-warnings 0`) |
| Config | Root `eslint.config.js` (`@eslint/js` recommended + `typescript-eslint` strictTypeChecked) |
| Scope | `packages/**`, `apps/**` — not `agent-rules/` harness copy |

Fix lint in the same change — never disable rules to silence without user approval.

## Library coverage policy (`packages/br-validators`)

| Rule | Requirement |
|------|-------------|
| Lines / branches / functions / statements | **100%** |
| Scope | **All** `src/**/*.ts` — including barrels (`index.ts`, `cnpj.ts`) |
| Test type | **Real tests** — official golden vectors from RFB/Bacen/CONTRAN |
| Forbidden | Mocking `validate*` / `format*` / check-digit logic; `@vitest/coverage` excludes to hide gaps |

Golden vectors live in `tests/vectors/*.official.json` — cite official source URL.

Example mandatory vector: CNPJ `12ABC34501DE35` (RFB FAQ Q14).

## CLI coverage

`apps/cli`: 100% on `src/**` (excluding `src/index.ts` bin shim only).

## Agent behavior

1. After editing `packages/br-validators/src/**`, run `pnpm --filter br-validators test:coverage`.
2. After any TS/TSX edit, run `pnpm lint`.
3. If coverage drops below 100%, add **real** tests — not snapshot-only or empty asserts.
4. Never claim "tests pass" without running commands.

## CI

GitHub Actions enforces the same gates — see `.github/workflows/ci.yml`.
